<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.washtimes.com/national/20020718-28606488.htm">www.washtimes.com/nationa...606488.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
I'm sure alot of people got lambasted for this fuck up in inter service communication and briefing proceedures. But it was Maj. Schmidt that disreguarded ROE and dropped the ordinance before being cleared. He's in a world of shit right now and deservedly so. He had all the time in the world to egress and assess the target.<br>
<br>
The real stink of it is that Umbach, who was the flight leader, makes the comment that they should 'make sure it's not friendlies'. This indicates to me that even though they didnt know about the training exercise, they were aware that friendlies might be operating in that area. But they still painted the target and dropped the bombs.<br>
<br>
This incident is wrong on so many levels. Schmidt is a shithot veteran pilot. The first question I would ask him was how he could have mistaken groundfire on tank hulks for triple A directed at the F16s? The second would be why didn't he take the time to make that assesment?<br>
<br>
It's sad to think of all the time and money spent to train and equip this guy. Sadder still to think that in spite of that training and equipment four Canadians are dead because of his lack of restraint. <br>
<br>
War sucks.<br>
